<CAPTION>  Map; MAP: Sam Hundley -- Mercury News; HEAVY TRAFFIC (and ALTERNATE ROUTES);
The solid black areas indicate heaviest traffic on a typical weekday during
the peak commute hours of 6 a.m. to 9 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. to 7 p.m. Congestion
is defined as traveling 35 miles per hour for 15 minutes (color).; SOURCE:
Caltrans  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  SF-BAY-AREA; TRAFFIC; TRANSPORTATION; ROAD; ALTERNATIVE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  NEXT time you're stuck in traffic, wondering why so many cars are crammed onto
Bay Area freeways, just try traveling a good distance without using
interstates 880 or 280 or the ever-popular Highway 101.;    Still, there are
times when going off the beaten path might make sense. We wondered what it
would be like to get to some popular spots around the Bay Area without using
major highways.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  THE ROADS LESS TRAVELED
TRAFFIC, SMOG, DELAYS -- ISN'T THERE ANOTHER
WAY TO GET WHERE YOU'RE GOING?  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  See also related story on page 8L of this section.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>      The results are on this map, and are hardly what you would call shortcuts
-- more like experiments in automotive stamina. But these alternate routes
will let you know what to expect if you decide to get off at the nearest exit,
vowing never to return.; ..............................; 1. From California
Avenue and El Camino Real in Palo Alto to the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk.;
Going westbound on California Avenue from the train station, turn left onto El
Camino Real. A. Take Page Mill Road, turning right toward Interstate 280.
Instead of getting onto 280, continue all the way to Skyline Boulevard. B.
Take a left onto Skyline, which turns into Summit Road. C. Take a quick right
onto Bear Creek Road. D. Immediately turn left onto Upper Zayante Road.
Continue on as it becomes Graham Hill Road, and finally Ocean Street once
within the Santa Cruz city limits, then; follow the signs to the beach
boardwalk.; Distance: 38 miles. Driving time: 1 hour, 30 minutes.;    ...; 2.
From El Camino Real in San Mateo to the Cow Palace in Daly City, then to
Candlestick Park and on to Union Square, Post and Powell streets, San
Francisco.; Starting at the intersection of Crystal Springs Road and El Camino
Real: A. Turn left onto northbound El Camino. B. Take a right onto San Mateo
Avenue in San Bruno. This street eventually becomes Bayshore Boulevard. C.
Turn left at Geneva Avenue in Daly City and follow to the Cow Palace.;
Distance: 13 miles. Driving time: 35 minutes.; For Candlestick, simply stay
straight on Bayshore. C. Turn right on Gilman Avenue and follow it toward the
bay to the park's back entrance, at which point you bear left.; Distance:
Slightly more than 3 additional miles. Driving time: an additional 5 minutes.;
For Union Square, go back to Geneva and take it northwest into the city. D.
Turn right on Mission Street. E. Take to Market and turn right. F. Take Market
to Van Ness and turn left. G. Turn right on Post Street. G. Take to Powell.;
Distance: An additional 8 miles (complete trip total: 24 miles) Driving time:
An additional 34 minutes (trip total is 1 hour, 14 minutes).; ...; 3. From
North Santa Cruz Avenue and Los  Gatos/Saratoga Road in Los Gatos to Lockheed
Missiles &amp; Space Company, 1111 Lockheed Way in Sunnyvale.; A. Go north on
North Santa Cruz Avenue A. Take a left onto Los Gatos/Saratoga Road. Follow
that into Saratoga until it becomes Saratoga/Sunnyvale Road. Follow it to
Sunnyvale. B.  Bear left toward where it becomes Mathilda Avenue in Sunnyvale.
C. Go past 101 and 237, then turn left on Moffett Park Drive, taking all the
way to Lockheed. Distance: 14 1/2 miles. Driving time: 27 minutes.; ...; 4.
From Meridian and Curtner avenues in San Jose to IBM on 5600 Cottle Road in
South San Jose.; From southbound Meridian, turn left onto Curtner. A. Turn
right onto Monterey Highway. B. Get off at Blossom Hill Road/Cottle Road and
follow the signs to IBM.; Distance: 10 miles. Driving time: 17 1/2 minutes.;
...; 5. From Hamilton and Bascom Avenues in  Campbell to Great America
amusement park in Santa Clara.; Heading north on Bascom, follow to where it
becomes Washington Street and then bear right onto Lafayette Street in Santa
Clara. A. Take a left onto Agnew Road. B. Take a right onto Mission College
Boulevard. C. Then a right onto Great America Parkway to the park. Distance: 9
1/2 miles. Driving time: 20 1/2 minutes.; ...; 6. Stevenson Boulevard in
Fremont to the Oakland Coliseum (This route will also take you to Oakland
International Airport).; Take Stevenson toward Highway 101 to Blacow Road. A.
Turn right on Blacow Road and follow to Thornton Avenue. B. Take that to
Newark Boulevard and turn right. This road eventually becomes Union City
Boulevard and then Hesperian Boulevard. C. Turn left to Grant Avenue in San
Lorenzo. D. Turn right on Washington Avenue. E. Make a quick left onto W.
Juana Avenue. F. Then a quick right onto San Leandro Boulevard. G. Then left
onto Davis street. H. Turn right onto Doolittle Drive. I. Then another right
onto Hegenberger Road and on to the Coliseum.; Distance: 30 miles. Driving
time: 1 hour, 5 minutes.; ...; 7. From Jefferson Avenue and Middlefield Road
in Redwood City to the Great America amusement park in Santa Clara.; Head
south on Middlefield. A. Follow it all the way to San Antonio Road in Mountain
View and turn right. B. Follow the signs to Alma Street south, this will
become Central Expressway. C. Take it through Santa Clara and taking a left
onto Scott Boulevard. D. Then take a right onto Montague Expressway. E. Then a
left onto Mission College Boulevard. F. Turn right onto Great America
Parkway.; Distance: 22 miles. Driving time: 43 minutes.; ...; 8. From Monroe
Street and Manchester Drive in Santa Clara to Raging Waters at Capitol
Expressway and Tully Road in San Jose.;    From southbound Monroe turn left
onto Manchester. A. Take a right on Washington Street. B. Turn left onto
Newhall Street. C. Turn right onto Park Avenue. D. Turn left on Naglee Street
E. Turn right onto The Alameda and stay on it as it becomes first Santa Clara
Street, then Alum Rock Avenue. F. At Capitol Avenue, turn right. Follow road
as it becomes Capitol Expressway, then take that to Tully Road and Raging
Waters.; Distance: 9 1/2 miles. Driving time: 28 minutes.; ...; 9. Bascom
Avenue in San Jose to Circle Star Center, 1717 Industrial Way in San Carlos.;
Take Bascom north to Moorpark Avenue. A. Turn left onto Moorpark, continuing
as it becomes Bollinger Road around Cupertino. B. Turn right on
Sunnyvale-Saratoga Road. C. Take a left onto Stevens Creek Boulevard. C. Take
a right onto Foothill Expressway and follow to where it becomes Junipero Serra
Boulevard in Palo Alto and then Alameda de las Pulgas through Menlo
Park/Atherton. D. Turn right at Howard Avenue. E. Take another right at
Industrial Way and go down to the Circle Star.; Distance: 27 miles. Driving
time: 1 hour, 7 minutes.  </TEXT>
